<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10727838>
    dc:description "Fig. 33. Mikro crassussp. nov. A–B. Holotype, apertural and oblique basal views (apex missing), diameter 2.9 mm (MNHN-IM-2000-38066). C. Apical view of juvenile specimen with intact apex, diameter 1.5 mm (paratype, MNHN-IM-2000-38067). D–E. Specimen with brown superficial deposit, diameter 1.7 mm (paratype, MNHN-IM-2000-38067). F. Protoconch of C, scale bar =100 μm. G. Composite image of holotype superimposed on apex of C, diameter 2.9 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10727838/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

